Package: rbcmodel
Title: Model Rubisco Carboxylation Rate Across Temperature, CO2, and O2
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Kaitlin", "Harrison", email = "k.harrison.sci@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    person("Wing-Ho", "Ko", email = "", role = "aut"))
Description: 'rbcmodel' collects published kinetics of Rubisco and uses these
    kinetics to model the carboxylation rate across CO2 and O2 concentrations
    and different temperatures. The carboxylation rate can be modeled as the
    gross rate or the net rate, which takes into account the oxygenase
    activity of the enzyme using one of the two known phosphoglycolate
    salvage pathways. Custom enzymes and temperature dependences can be
    created with user kinetics, or published kinetics can be accessed through
    a meta-analysis contained within the package.
